    				Research    			
  			

  			
  			
  			
    			Ramesh has addressed several challenging problems in his research career in many diverse areas ranging from control theory to experiential computing. He enjoys addressing new challenging problems that are the result of advances in technology and can be solved using novel concepts and new technology. He is particularly interested in areas that combine real time data, perception, and social networks. One of his passions is to consider information independent of medium and use it for managing real time societal problems.
Some of the traditional areas that he has contributed and helped shape are:

Computer Vision
Multimedia Information Management
Experiential Computing
    			  			

  			


	
	
			

		
	



	   

	   
	   	
	   
	   
			



